For the cod: Preheat the oven to 450°F. Rub the fish with olive oil, sprinkle with salt and pepper, and place in a lightly oiled pan. Place the pan in the middle or upper third of the oven and roast 12 to 15 minutes, depending on thickness. To serve: Divide the confit into 6 portions and place on serving plates, Place a cod fillet on top of each portion and drizzle 1 tablespoon basil oil around it. Variation: For the cod, substitute 6 whole snapper, 1 to 1¼ pounds each, stuffed with 2 springs thyme each.